The paper discusses the use of graphics processors for scientific computing, specifically for fast summation algorithms. This falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves algorithmic redesign, which could fall under the categories of scientific computing (cs.SC) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). Finally, the paper discusses performance improvements, which could fall under the category of measurement and analysis of algorithms and complexity (cs.MS).
